d60 60
a119 50
    <p>
    <dt> Install the <i>Java Run Time Environment</i> by executing: 
         <i>j2re-1_4_2_06-linux-i586.bin</i> </dt> 
    <dd> <b> chmod a+x j2re-1_4_2_06-linux-i586.bin</b> </dd> 
    <dd> <b> j2re-1_4_2_06-linux-i586.bin</b> </dd>
    <dd> Agree to license terms. </dd></p>

    <p>
    <dt> Install the <i>Java Advanced Imaging Run Time Environment</i> by executing: 
         <i>jai-1_1_2_01-lib-linux-i586-jre.bin</i> </dt>
    <dd> <b>cd j2re1.4.2_06/</b> </dd>  
    <dd> <b>chmod u+x ../jai-1_1_2_01-lib-linux-i586-jre.bin</b> </dd>  
    <dd> <b>../jai-1_1_2_01-lib-linux-i586-jre.bin</b> </dd>
    <dd> Agree to license terms. </dd></p>

    <p>
    <dt><b>If you are  using the 'C' shell, the next three tasks can be alternatively 
         be done by editing the first line in: <i>jweb.cshrc</i> as instructed
         therein and then placing the contents of <i>jweb.cshrc</i>
         in your <i>.cshrc</i> startup file.</b></dt> </p>

    <p> 
    <dt> Create <i>$JWEB_DIR</i> environment variable specifying location for <i>jweb</i>.</dt>
    <dd>If you are  using the 'C' shell, this can be done with <i>setenv</i> 
        in your <i>.cshrc</i> startup file.</dd>    
    <dd><b>setenv &nbsp; JWEB_DIR &nbsp;   Substitute_path_of_your_jweb_directory_here </b></dd></p>

    <p> 
    <dt> Add Java libraries to <i>$CLASSPATH & $LD_LIBRARY_PATH<i> by </dt>
    <dd><b>setenv &nbsp; JAIHOME   &nbsp; $JWEB_DIR/j2re1.4.2_06/lib</b></dd>
    <dd><b>setenv &nbsp; CLASSPATH &nbsp; $JAIHOME/ext/jai_core.jar:$JAIHOME/ext/jai_codec.jar:$CLASSPATH</b></dd>
    <dd><b>#NOTE:</b> &nbsp;  if CLASSPATH is not defined before then use :</dd>
    <dd>#setenv &nbsp; CLASSPATH &nbsp; $JAIHOME/ext/jai_core.jar:$JAIHOME/ext/jai_codec.jar</dd>
    <dd><b>setenv &nbsp; CLASSPATH &nbsp; $JAIHOME/ext/mlibwrapper.jar:$CLASSPATH</b></dd>
    <dd><b>setenv &nbsp; CLASSPATH &nbsp; $JWEB_DIR/WEB.jar:$CLASSPATH</b></dd>
    <dd><b>setenv &nbsp; LD_LIBRARY_PATH &nbsp; $LD_LIBRARY_PATH/:$JAIHOME/ext/:$CLASSPATH</b></dd>
    <dd><b>#NOTE:</b> &nbsp;  if LD_LIBRARY_PATH is not defined before then use :</dd>
    <dd>#setenv &nbsp; LD_LIBRARY_PATH &nbsp; $JAIHOME/ext/:$CLASSPATH</b></dd></p>

    <p> 
    <dt> Create <i>jweb</i> command with specified location and desired run-time
         memory allocation.</dt>
    <dd>If you are  using the 'C' shell, this can be done with an <i>alias</i> line 
        in your <i>.cshrc</i> startup file.</dd>    
    <dd> <b>alias  &nbsp; jweb  &nbsp;'$JWEB_DIR/j2re1.4.2_06/bin/java &nbsp; &nbsp;  -Xmx512m -Djava.util.prefs.syncInterval=2000000 web/StartWeb' </b></dd></p>
    <dd> Note that: <i>512m</i> represents the maximum megabytes memory allowed 
          for this JAVA application. 
          If your machine has more or less installed memory, you should change it accordingly.</dd>
    </dl>

